{
  "texts": [
    "The Coffee Bean Dataset is a collection of information about coffee beans from around the world that is shown in Fig. 2.",
    "It includes data on the origin, type, and flavor profile of each bean, as well as information on the growing conditions and processing techniques used to produce them.",
    "The images are automatically collected and saved in PNG format, with 4800 images in total, classified into 4 degrees of roasting, with 1200 images under each degree that are illustrated in Table 2.",
    "We went with the Coffee Bean Dataset for our study because it's got a solid stash of details about coffee beans from all sorts of places worldwide.",
    "We wanted to dig into the specifics of various coffee beans-where they come from, what kind they are, their flavor, how they grow, and how they're processed."
  ]
}